I tell you where the novel Zurich comes. Zurich is actually the Bay Area. In

00:13.740 --> 00:26.840
some sense anyway. Not literally. But the fact is that I live in the hills of
Oakland in the East Bay. And there's a drive along the ridge of the hills. And I

00:26.840 --> 00:38.840
was up there one evening just at dusk. when the light is such that the bay
itself, which you can look down on, you'll see San Francisco and Marin County

00:38.840 --> 00:50.680
across the bay, and San Jose to the south, and Berkeley and Oakland in front of
