12:37.660 --> 12:45.620
hat. It's been done in science fiction for 50 years. You get embarrassed with
this person. John Updike did a short story in New Yorker about three years ago,

12:45.680 --> 12:57.080
and it was just embarrassing because he obviously didn't know the field. so I
think that anybody who is writing science fiction today should simply approach

12:57.080 --> 13:10.280
it as telling the very best story that he or she can and not underestimating the
